Carboxylated nitrile rubber, also known as XNBR, is witnessing significant demand in various applications. The market can be segmented by application, end-use industry, and region. In terms of application, carboxylated nitrile rubber finds its use in hoses & belts, sealants, adhesives, industrial rubber goods, among others. The versatility of this material allows it to cater to a wide range of industries. When considering end-use industries, automotive, construction, industrial, oil & gas, and others are the major sectors driving the demand for carboxylated nitrile rubber. Geographically, the market is spread across regions such as North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa.

